Sentencas: Cobalt-containing cathodes are known for their ability to operate under high-temperature applications in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Short review on cobalt-free cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Reducing the operation temperature into intermediate temperature-to-low temperature (IT-LT) zones may lead to a mismatch in the thermal expansion coefficient between the cathodes and the developed IT-LTSOFC electrolyte materials.
Titulo: Short review on cobalt-free cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Hence, cathode materials are adjusted to resolve this issue.
Titulo: Short review on cobalt-free cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Studies on IT-LTSOFC propose cobalt-free cathodes as an alternative way to produce high electro-chemical performance cells for operation within the IT-LT range.
Titulo: Short review on cobalt-free cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Novel cobalt-free cathode powders are developed using perovskite structured materials, such as strontium ferrite oxide, as the main components together with dopants.
Titulo: Short review on cobalt-free cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This paper reviews various studies on cobalt-free cathode development, including the most important parameter in determining cathode performance, namely, the polarization resistance of SOFC cathodes.
Titulo: Short review on cobalt-free cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells
